questions.text:
Match the specific formed elements of blood listed in Column I with their characteristic functional roles or features listed in Column II, and select the correct option representing the clinical profile of a healthy individual.

 egin{itemize}
    \item[] 	extbf{Column I}
    \item[(a)] Basophils
    \item[(b)] Neutrophils
    \item[(c)] Eosinophils
    \item[(d)] Lymphocytes
\end{itemize}

 egin{itemize}
    \item[] 	extbf{Column II}
    \item[(i)] Phagocytic cells that destroy foreign organisms
    \item[(ii)] Secrete histamine, serotonin, and heparin
    \item[(iii)] Resist infections and are associated with allergic reactions
    \item[(iv)] Responsible for immune responses of the body
\end{itemize}
